article.headline: Sacramento State 66, UC Riverside 55
article.story: SACRAMENTO (AP) -- Joseth Dawson's 15 points and Chris Lange's 10 rebounds helped lift host Sacramento State to a 66-55 victory over UC Riverside Monday. Ricky Porter had 13 points to lead the Highlanders (3-5), who are 0-5 on the road this season. After opening the game with four dunks in seven minutes, the Hornets (6-6) built up a 27-19 lead when Jameel Pugh hit a basket with 3:45 left in the first half. UC Riverside countered with an 8-3 run to make the score 30-27 after Mark Peters hit a lay up with one minute left. But E.J. Harris, who had 10 points in 17 minutes of play, hit a jump shot with eight seconds left to give the Sacramento a 32-27 half-time lead. In the second half, the Highlanders battled back to pull within four points after Vili Morton hit two Cedric Thompkins foul shots, making the score 55-51 at the 5:07 mark. The Hornets finished the game with an 11-4 run. The Hornets, who missed both of their free-throw shots in the first half of play, went 13-for-19 in the second half. Sacramento State has claimed four of five victories against Big West Conference foes this season.
